<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0"/>
  <title>Baby Shower Photography</title>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/Baby shower photographyCss.css"/>
  <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Playfair+Display:wght@600&family=Open+Sans&display=swap" rel="stylesheet"/>
</head>
<body>

  <header class="hero-section-babeshowpics photo-hero-babeshowpics">
    <div class="hero-content-babeshowpics fade-in-up-babeshowpics">
      <h1>Capture Every Magical Moment</h1>
      <p>From glowing moms-to-be to joyful guests, here's how to make the memories last.</p>
    </div>
  </header>

  <section class="tips-box fade-in-up">
  <h2>Photography Tips</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Use natural lighting to enhance soft colors and sweet expressions.</li>
    <li>Capture candid interactions and unposed giggles — they make the best memories.</li>
    <li>Include detail shots: tiny feet, gifts, cupcakes, and decorations.</li>
    <li>Take wide shots of the decorated space before guests arrive — it captures the mood and effort put into planning.</li>
    <li>Get close-up shots of handwritten notes or cards for a sentimental touch.</li>
    <li>Photograph the gift-opening moment and the reactions — these are priceless memories.</li>
    <li>Include group photos with family and friends, but keep them relaxed and joyful.</li>
    <li>Try overhead shots of the dessert or gift tables for a styled, editorial look.</li>
    <li>Sneak in behind-the-scenes photos — a parent adjusting baby socks or friends laughing in the kitchen.</li>
  </ul>
</section>


  <section class="photo-gallery">
    <h2>Moments to Remember</h2>
    <div class="grid fade-in-up">
      <img src="/img/mom to be smiling.jpeg" alt="Mom-to-be smiling">
      <img src="/img/guest laughing.jpeg" alt="Guests laughing">
      <img src="/img/table decor.jpeg" alt="Decor and table setup">
      <img src="/img/cake cutting.jpeg" alt="Cake cutting">
      <img src="/img/Baby Shower Props.jpeg" alt="Baby themed props">
      <img src="/img/group photo.jpeg" alt="Group photo">
    </div>
  </section>

</body>
